name: Vector1

unions.name: Index
unions.comment: All the indices to a `Vector1 a`. There are exactly 1 of them. Its kind of like an `Int` except there is a finite amount of them.

aliases.name: Vector1
aliases.comment: A vector that contains exactly 1 elements

values.name: cons
values.comment:
Add an element to the front of a vector, incrementing the vector size by 1

    Vector4.cons -1 (Vector4.from4 0 1 2 3)
    --> Vector5.from5 -1 0 1 2 3

values.name: foldl
values.comment: Reduce a `Vector1 a` from the left.
values.type: (a -> b -> b) -> b -> Vector1.Vector1 a -> b

values.name: foldr
values.comment: Reduce a `Vector1 a` from the right.
values.type: (a -> b -> b) -> b -> Vector1.Vector1 a -> b

values.name: from1
values.comment: Make a `Vector1 a` from 1 elements

values.name: fromList
values.comment:
Turn a `List a` into a `Vector1 a`. If there are not enough items in the `List a`, then this function returns `Nothing`. The extra items in the input list, if there are any, is returned as the first element in the output tuple.

    Vector3.fromList []
    --> Nothing

    Vector3.fromList [ 1 ]
    --> Nothing

    Vector3.fromList [ 5, 6, 7, 8 ]
    --> Just ([ 8 ], Vector3.from3 5 6 7)
values.type: List.List a -> Maybe.Maybe ( List.List a, Vector1.Vector1 a )

values.name: fromListWithDefault
values.comment:
Turn a `List a` into a `Vector1 a`. If there are not enough items in the `List a`, then fill in the remaining spots with a default value. The extra items in the input list, if there are any, is returned as the first element in the output tuple.

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 1 []
    --> ([] ,Vector3.from3 1 1 1)

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 2 [ 1 ]
    --> ([], Vector3.from3 1 2 2)

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 2 [ 5, 6, 7, 8 ]
    --> ([ 8 ], Vector3.from3 5 6 7)
values.type: a -> List.List a -> ( List.List a, Vector1.Vector1 a )

values.name: get
values.comment: Get the item at that `Index` in a `Vector1 a`

values.name: group
values.comment:
Break a `List a` down into groups of `Vector1 a`. The output is a tuple, where the left side is a list of the remainder.

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3 ]
    --> ([] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4 ]
    --> ([ 4 ] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 ]
    --> ([ 4, 5 ] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 ]
    --> ([] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3, Vector3.from3 4 5 6 ])
values.type: List.List a -> ( List.List a, List.List (Vector1.Vector1 a) )

values.name: indexToInt
values.comment: Turn the `Index` into an `Int`

values.name: indexedMap
values.comment: Apply a function on every element with its index as first argument
values.type: (Vector1.Index -> a -> b) -> Vector1.Vector1 a -> Vector1.Vector1 b

values.name: indices
values.comment: A list of all the indices, from 0 to 0

values.name: initializeFromIndex
values.comment: Make a `Vector1 a` using a function that takes an `Index`

values.name: initializeFromInt
values.comment: Make a `Vector1 a` using a function that takes an `Int`, representing the index

values.name: intToIndex
values.comment:
Try and turn an `Int` into an `Index`, returning `Nothing` if the `Int` is above the maximum index, or below the zero index, of this `Vector1 a`

        Vector5.intToIndex 4
        --> Just Vector5.Index4

        Vector3.intToIndex 4
        --> Nothing

values.name: length
values.comment: The length of this vector type, which is 1

values.comment: Apply a function to every element in a `Vector1 a`.

values.comment: Given an index, get the next one. Unless its the last index in which case there is no next index (`Nothing`)

Turn a `List a` into a `Vector43 a`. If there are not enough items in the `List a`, then this function returns `Nothing`. The extra items in the input list, if there are any, is returned as the first element in the output tuple.

    Vector3.fromList []
    --> Nothing

    Vector3.fromList [ 1 ]
    --> Nothing

    Vector3.fromList [ 5, 6, 7, 8 ]
    --> Just ([ 8 ], Vector3.from3 5 6 7)
values.type: List.List a -> Maybe.Maybe ( List.List a, Vector43.Vector43 a )

values.name: fromListWithDefault
values.comment:
Turn a `List a` into a `Vector43 a`. If there are not enough items in the `List a`, then fill in the remaining spots with a default value. The extra items in the input list, if there are any, is returned as the first element in the output tuple.

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 1 []
    --> ([] ,Vector3.from3 1 1 1)

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 2 [ 1 ]
    --> ([], Vector3.from3 1 2 2)

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 2 [ 5, 6, 7, 8 ]
    --> ([ 8 ], Vector3.from3 5 6 7)
values.type: a -> List.List a -> ( List.List a, Vector43.Vector43 a )

values.name: group
values.comment:

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3 ]
    --> ([] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4 ]
    --> ([ 4 ] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 ]
    --> ([ 4, 5 ] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 ]
    --> ([] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3, Vector3.from3 4 5 6 ])

values.name: fromList

    --> Nothing

values.name: fromListWithDefault

    --> ([] ,Vector3.from3 1 1 1)

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 2 [ 1 ]
    --> ([], Vector3.from3 1 2 2)

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 2 [ 5, 6, 7, 8 ]
    --> ([ 8 ], Vector3.from3 5 6 7)

Add an element to the front of a vector, incrementing the vector size by 1

    Vector4.cons -1 (Vector4.from4 0 1 2 3)
    --> Vector5.from5 -1 0 1 2 3

values.name: foldl
values.comment: Reduce a `Vector8 a` from the left.
values.type: (a -> b -> b) -> b -> Vector8.Vector8 a -> b

values.name: foldr
values.comment: Reduce a `Vector8 a` from the right.
values.type: (a -> b -> b) -> b -> Vector8.Vector8 a -> b

values.name: from8
values.comment: Make a `Vector8 a` from 8 elements
values.type: a -> a -> a -> a -> a -> a -> a -> a -> Vector8.Vector8 a

values.name: fromList
values.comment:
Turn a `List a` into a `Vector8 a`. If there are not enough items in the `List a`, then this function returns `Nothing`. The extra items in the input list, if there are any, is returned as the first element in the output tuple.

    Vector3.fromList []
    --> Nothing

    Vector3.fromList [ 1 ]
    --> Nothing

    Vector3.fromList [ 5, 6, 7, 8 ]
    --> Just ([ 8 ], Vector3.from3 5 6 7)
values.type: List.List a -> Maybe.Maybe ( List.List a, Vector8.Vector8 a )

values.name: fromListWithDefault
values.comment:
Turn a `List a` into a `Vector8 a`. If there are not enough items in the `List a`, then fill in the remaining spots with a default value. The extra items in the input list, if there are any, is returned as the first element in the output tuple.

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 1 []
    --> ([] ,Vector3.from3 1 1 1)

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 2 [ 1 ]
    --> ([], Vector3.from3 1 2 2)

    Vector3.fromListWithDefault 2 [ 5, 6, 7, 8 ]
    --> ([ 8 ], Vector3.from3 5 6 7)
values.type: a -> List.List a -> ( List.List a, Vector8.Vector8 a )

values.name: get
values.comment: Get the item at that `Index` in a `Vector8 a`

values.name: group
values.comment:
Break a `List a` down into groups of `Vector8 a`. The output is a tuple, where the left side is a list of the remainder.

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3 ]
    --> ([] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4 ]
    --> ([ 4 ] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 ]
    --> ([ 4, 5 ] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3 ])

    Vector3.group [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 ]
    --> ([] , [ Vector3.from3 1 2 3, Vector3.from3 4 5 6 ])
values.type: List.List a -> ( List.List a, List.List (Vector8.Vector8 a) )

values.name: indexToInt
values.comment: Turn the `Index` into an `Int`

values.name: indexedMap
values.comment: Apply a function on every element with its index as first argument
values.type: (Vector8.Index -> a -> b) -> Vector8.Vector8 a -> Vector8.Vector8 b

values.name: indices
values.comment: A list of all the indices, from 0 to 7

values.name: initializeFromIndex
values.comment: Make a `Vector8 a` using a function that takes an `Index`

values.name: initializeFromInt
values.comment: Make a `Vector8 a` using a function that takes an `Int`, representing the index

values.name: intToIndex
values.comment:
Try and turn an `Int` into an `Index`, returning `Nothing` if the `Int` is above the maximum index, or below the zero index, of this `Vector8 a`

        Vector5.intToIndex 4
        --> Just Vector5.Index4

        Vector3.intToIndex 4
        --> Nothing

values.name: length
values.comment: The length of this vector type, which is 8

values.comment: Apply a function to every element in a `Vector8 a`.

values.type: (a -> b -> c) -> Vector8.Vector8 a -> Vector8.Vector8 b -> Vector8.Vector8 c

values.type: (a -> b -> c -> d) -> Vector8.Vector8 a -> Vector8.Vector8 b -> Vector8.Vector8 c -> Vector8.Vector8 d

values.name: map4
values.type: (a -> b -> c -> d -> e) -> Vector8.Vector8 a -> Vector8.Vector8 b -> Vector8.Vector8 c -> Vector8.Vector8 d -> Vector8.Vector8 e

values.name: mapItem
values.comment: Transform just one particular item at a particular `Index`
values.type: Vector8.Index -> (a -> a) -> Vector8.Vector8 a -> Vector8.Vector8 a

values.name: member
values.comment: See if a Vector8 a contains a value

values.name: nextIndex
values.comment: Given an index, get the next one. Unless its the last index in which case there is no next index (`Nothing`)

values.name: pop
values.comment:
Separate a `Vector8 a` into its last element and everything else.

    Vector4.pop (Vector4.from4 0 1 2 3)
    --> (Vector3.from3 0 1 2, 3)

values.name: previousIndex
values.comment: Given an index, get the previous one. Unless its the `0` index in which case there is no previous index (`Nothing`)

values.name: push
values.comment:
Add an element to the end of a `Vector8 a`, incrementing its size by 1

    Vector4.push 4 (Vector4.from4 0 1 2 3)
    --> Vector5.from5 0 1 2 3 4

values.name: repeat
values.comment: Make a `Vector8 a` filled with just one item repeated over and over again.

values.name: reverse
values.comment: Reverse the order of the items in a `Vector8 a`

values.name: set
values.comment: Set the item at a specific index in a `Vector8 a`
values.type: Vector8.Index -> a -> Vector8.Vector8 a -> Vector8.Vector8 a

values.name: toIndexedList
values.comment: Turn a `Vector8 a` elm into a list, where each element is paired with its `Index`

values.name: toList
values.comment: Convert a `Vector8 a` into a `List a` of length 8

values.name: uncons
values.comment:
Split a `Vector8 a` into its first element and the rest

    Vector4.uncons (Vector4.from4 0 1 2 3)
    --> (0, Vector3.from3 1 2 3)
